# Coding Conventions

**TypeScript**: Named exports (default only where Next.js requires). Explicit return types on exports. No `any`. Use `satisfies`. Early returns over nested `if/else`.

**Functions**: `function` declarations for all definitions. Arrow functions only for inline callbacks.

**Comments**: One-line JSDoc on every export (WHAT not HOW). Inline `//` only for WHY. No `@param`/`@returns`. No commented-out code. `// TODO: description`.

**Server Actions**: `'use server'` at top. Zod validate inputs. Return `{ success: true, data }` or `{ success: false, error }`. `revalidatePath`/`revalidateTag` after mutations.

**API Routes**: Zod validate at top. `{ data }` or `{ error: { code, message } }`. Try/catch + `logger.error()`. Correct status codes.

**Zod**: Co-export schema + inferred type. `.describe()` for LLM fields. Strict AI schemas.

**Tests**: Sentence test names. AAA pattern. MSW for external APIs (no `vi.mock()`). `.integration.test.ts` suffix. Colocated.

**Errors**: Custom classes with `cause` chaining. Generic user messages. Always log.

**Logging**: `logger` only (never console). Structured context. Correct levels (error/warn/info/debug).

**Files**: kebab-case. `.tsx` only for JSX. `@/` alias for imports. Inline type imports.

## Rule Maintenance

These rules are maintained manually. The user will periodically ask the AI to review them for accuracy. Never modify `.mdc` files without explicit user approval.
